photos.text: The Lord Mayor of Perth J.T. Franklin and the Governor Sir William Campion speak at the event celebrating the centenary of W.A. The Governor unveiled the Centenary Tablet on the western corner of the�Town Hall.
photos.title: Crowd and parade outside Perth Town Hall celebrating Western Australia's Centenary

photos.text: published in the Western Mail 29 April 1926, p.3 (Supplement) with caption: The Most Rev. Dr Mannix D.D. (Archbishop of Melbourne) speaking. Among those on the platform are the Most Rev. Patrick Clune C.S.S.R. D.D. (Archbishop of Perth), Most Rev. Francis M. Redwood (Archbishop of Wellington, N.Z.), Most Rev. R. W. Spence, D. D. (Archbishop of Adelaide), Most Rev. J. Duhig D.D. (Archbishop of Brisbane), Most Rev. M. Sheehan (Coadjutor Archbishop of Sydney) and the bishops of Sandhurst, Wilcannia-Forbes, Ballarat and Port Augusta.
photos.title: Archbishop Mannix addressing the crowd at the laying of the foundation stone for extensions to St Mary's Cathedral

photos.text: A sign advertises R.A. Jones (in the Post Office Directory Mrs R.A. Jones) as proprietor of the Royal Hotel opposite the Universal Shoe Stores. By the 1926 W.A. Post Office Directory the licensee of the Royal Hotel is M.E. Coombes.
